INSERT INTO `Blog` VALUES (1,'Ranji Trophy: Ignored and irrelevant','Indian cricket’s humiliation in two successive overseas tours would call for some serious introspection.','',5,5,'http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/One-World/entry/ranji-trophy-ignored-and-irrelevant','2012-03-07 07:56:56'),(2,'Spectator support for the REAL Team India is heartening','The redeeming factor was the support the game has started receiving from the crowds.','',10,1,'http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/randomaccess/entry/spectator-support-for-the-real-team-india-is-heartening','2012-03-07 07:57:03'),(3,'An unqualified success!','Sure, Indian fans and the media burst into ecstasy after the team made sure that there would be no repeat of the tragedy at Santiago, Chile, four years ago when India lost to Great Britain 0-2 in the final.','',10,1,'http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/spot-kick/entry/an-unqualified-success','2012-03-07 07:57:07'),(4,'Indian soccer: A world-class bubble!','But if we follow EPL, Champions League, Euro, World Cup and other soccer, it means we have football talent! That\'s setting new benchmark for logical thinking.','',7,1,'http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Tie-Breaker/entry/indian-soccer-a-world-class-bubble','2012-03-07 07:57:12'),(5,'India pay the price for running in circles','So is it really surprising that India kept collapsing in the triseries, and eventually crashed out of it too?','',5,5,'http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Between-the-Lies/entry/india-pay-the-price-for-running-in-circles','2012-03-07 07:57:19'),(0,'The subjectivity of victory & defeat Santosh Desai','This victory ensures that the Indian performance at the Olympics will be followed with great enthusiasm, and perhaps pave the way for renewed interest in what was once India\'s premier game.','',10,1,'http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Citycitybangbang/entry/the-subjectivity-of-victory-defeat','2012-03-07 08:02:26'),(0,'A battle for survival & pride: Do Sachin & Ponting need to prove their worth?','Having achieved almost everything in their careers, both Ricky Ponting and Sachin Tendulkar look like they are battling to prove they are good enough to be in the team, why?','',5,5,'http://www.indiansportsnews.com/isn-blogs/2012/02/21/11-a-battle-for-survival-a-pride-do-sachin-a-ponting-need-to-prove-their-worth.html','2012-03-07 08:03:25'),(0,'Curb the overdose menace to save Indian cricket','Over the past few years, Indian cricket is being constantly plagued by cricket overdose. And this is not doing any good for the game in the country rather it is proving detrimental to the game.','',5,5,'http://www.indiansportsnews.com/isn-blogs/2012/02/23/13-curb-the-overdose-menace-to-save-indian-cricket.html','2012-03-07 08:04:10'),(0,'Empty Dhyan Chand Stadium during Olympic Qualifiers gives a gloomy sight','Hero Motocorp’s new ad “Phir Dil Do Hockey Ko” is one of the most inspiring ads of all time','',10,1,'http://www.indiansportsnews.com/isn-blogs/2012/02/24/14-empty-dhyan-chand-stadium-during-olympic-qualifiers-gives-a-gloomy-sight.html','2012-03-07 08:05:57');
